An analysis of angry comments on Twitter by rail passengers has suggested the least popular train company in Britain was South West Trains.

The train company had the largest percentage of outright complaints in tweets by its customers, according to a survey of 92,000 messages by social media monitoring company Brandwatch.

SWT, which operates trains from London’s Waterloo station to Surrey, Hampshire and Dorset, attracted 44 per cent of all the tweets included in the study.

