A total of 36 per cent of the SWT tweets were outright complaints.

According to the study, First Great Western was the next least popular company, followed by Southeastern.

The company with the most positive tweets was East Coast.

Overall, 29,000 tweets were negative, with only five per cent being positive.

According to the study, the top five complaints were late-running trains, no air conditioning, broken down trains, being late for work and the rush-hour crush.

Joel Windels, lead community manager for Brandwatch said: 'It’s no surprise that people love to moan about public transport in Britain. It’s up there with the weather as one of the things we like to grumble about most.

